Inspired Sneak Attack		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Investigator ~ Studied Strike,TYPE.Sneak Attack																																																																																	PRETEXT:Inspiration pool; sneak attack or studied strike class feature.														PREVARGTEQ:InvestigatorInspirationPoolBonus,1																																						DESC:Your brilliant insight makes you more dangerous in combat.																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.11																								BENEFIT:When dealing sneak attack or studied strike damage, you can expend a use of inspiration from your pool to reroll all of your sneak attack dice that resulted in 1s. If you have the powerful sneak rogue talent, you can reroll all your sneak attack dice that resulted in 1s rather than treat them as 2s. If you have the deadly sneak advanced rogue talent, all 1s and 2s on your sneak attack damage dice can be rerolled. In either case, you must take the result of the rerolls, even if it's worse than the original result.
Kitsune Style			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Dirty Trick																																	PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13],[PREVARGTEQ:DirtyTricksterIntQualify,1]																																									PRETEXT:Int 13, Combat Expertise, Improved Dirty Trick.																																																													DESC:Your quick movement and trickery allow you to catch opponents off guard.																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.15																								BENEFIT:While using this style, you can attempt to perform a dirty trick in place of an attack at the end of a charge.
Kitsune Tricks			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Dirty Trick,Kitsune Style																														PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13],[PREVARGTEQ:DirtyTricksterIntQualify,1]	PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:3],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,3]																															PRETEXT:Int 13; Combat Expertise; Improved Dirty Trick; Kitsune Style; base attack bonus +3 or monk level 3rd.																																																				DESC:Your quick wit and even quicker maneuvers leave your opponents reeling.																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.15																								BENEFIT:While you are using the Kitsune Style feat, you can apply two different conditions with a single dirty trick combat maneuver check. Removing both conditions imparted in this way requires only one action.
Kitsune Vengeance			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:4,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Dirty Trick,Kitsune Style,Kitsune Tricks																												PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13],[PREVARGTEQ:DirtyTricksterIntQualify,1]	PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:6],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,6]																															PRETEXT:Int 13; Combat Expertise; Improved Dirty Trick; Kitsune Style; Kitsune Tricks; base attack bonus +6 or monk level 6th.																																																	DESC:You cleverly hide your attacks within your devious antics.																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.15																								BENEFIT:While using the Kitsune Style feat, when a foe provokes an attack of opportunity from you, you can attempt to perform a dirty trick combat maneuver in place of making a melee attack.
Lightning Rager			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Rage																																																																																								PRETEXT:Rage class feature.																																																																		DESC:Your primal instincts prevent you from being surprised.																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.13																								BENEFIT:If caught unawares during a surprise round, you can enter a rage as an immediate action. If you do, you gain a +2 insight bonus to your Armor Class for the remainder of the surprise round.
Master Sniper			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Expert Sniper,Rapid Shot																																																																													PRESKILL:1,Stealth=6							PRETEXT:Expert Sniper, Rapid Shot, Stealth 6 ranks.																																																														DESC:Your sniping is quick enough that you can fire a small volley unnoticed.																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.11																								BENEFIT:While hiding, you can make two ranged attacks at your highest attack bonus as a full-round action and then immediately use Stealth again. You take the normal penalties on your Stealth check to remain hidden. Effects that modify sniping apply to this full-round action. These attack rolls take a -2 penalty.
Poison Shot Deed			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Grit																																														PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Gunslinger ~ Grit],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Amateur Gunslinger]																																	PRETEXT:Amateur Gunslinger or grit class feature.																																																														DESC:You can specially prepare bullets to deliver poisons that are normally used more subtly.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.9																								BENEFIT:You can spend 1 grit point to load your firearm with 1 dose of inhaled or ingested poison as a move action. This action has no chance of exposing you to the poison (as if you had the poison use class feature). Shooting a firearm loaded with a poison in this manner sprays out the poison in a 15-foot cone. Any creatures caught in the blast take no damage but are exposed to this poison and must each immediately attempt a save against the poison as though the onset time had elapsed.
Powerful Poisoning		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Power Attack																																					PREMULT:1,[PRESKILL:1,Craft (Poison)=3],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Poison Use]																																					PRETEXT:Power Attack; Craft (poison) 3 ranks or poison use class feature.																																																										DESC:You can make powerful attacks that place more of your weapon's poison into a target's wounds.																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.6																								BENEFIT:When you damage an opponent with a Power Attack while using a poisoned weapon, you can forgo the bonus damage from Power Attack to increase the save DC of the poison by 1. When your base attack bonus reaches +4, and every +4 thereafter, the bonus to the poison's save DC increases by an additional 1. This can't cause the save DC to exceed %1.|floor(TL/2)+15
Reflexive Caster			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Reflexes																							PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=5,Divine=5,Psychic=5																																																									PRETEXT:Combat Reflexes, caster level 5th.																																																															DESC:You are ready to defend yourself with a spell at a moment's notice.																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.13																								BENEFIT:If you fail a Perception check that results in you being unable to act in a surprise round, you still roll initiative normally. You can act on your initiative count in the surprise round, but can only take a standard action to cast an abjuration spell that targets only yourself.
Scurrying Swarmer			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ratfolk ~ Swarming																																																																					PRERACE:1,Ratfolk,RACESUBTYPE=Ratfolk											PRETEXT:Ratfolk, swarming racial trait.																																																																DESC:You abandon all notion of personal space when in danger, scurrying about your allies in search of the best vantage point from which to strike at your foes.																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.23																								BENEFIT:You can use your swarming racial trait to enter the square of any willing ally the same size as you or one size category larger, granting you the benefits of the swarming trait as if your ally also had it. Your ally gains no benefits from sharing its space with you unless it also has the swarming racial trait. Additionally, you treat any ally who shares its space with you as having the same teamwork feats that you do. Your ally doesn't gain any of the bonuses from these feats unless she actually has the teamwork feats. You and your ally's positioning and actions must still meet the prerequisites in order to gain the teamwork feat's bonus, but your ally is considered to be adjacent to you while you share her space for the purpose of determining whether you or your ally gains a benefit.
Sneaking Critical			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Critical	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Sneak Attack	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Critical Focus																																																																															PRETEXT:Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9, sneak attack class feature.										PRETOTALAB:5																																														DESC:Your critical hits are particularly deadly.																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.11																								BENEFIT:Whenever you confirm a critical hit on a sneak attack, you can roll an additional number of sneak attack dice equal to your weapon's critical modifier. Special: You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.
Superior Dirty Trick		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Greater Dirty Trick,Improved Dirty Trick																													PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13],[PREVARGTEQ:DirtyTricksterIntQualify,1]																																									PRETEXT:Int 13, Combat Expertise, Greater Dirty Trick, Improved Dirty Trick, base attack bonus +8.						PRETOTALAB:8																																														DESC:Your training in a particular dirty trick makes it especially effective.															STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:STRING|Blinded|Dazzled|Deafened|Entangled|Shaken|Sickened																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.15																								BENEFIT:Choose one condition imposed by the dirty trick combat maneuver, such as blinded or entangled. The target must spend a full-round action in order to remove that condition. Special: You can gain this feat multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a different condition.
Terrifying Assault		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Frightening Ambush																																																																														PRESKILL:1,Intimidate=5							PRETEXT:Frightening Ambush, Intimidate 5 ranks.																																																															DESC:Your foes flee when you appear suddenly.																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.13																								BENEFIT:When using Intimidate to demoralize an opponent during a surprise round, if you exceed the DC by 10 or more, you can make the target frightened for 1 round instead of shaken.
Toxic Spell				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Metamagic		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Poison Use																						PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,Divine=2,Psychic=2																																															PRESKILL:1,Craft (Poison)=3						PRETEXT:Craft (poison) 5 ranks, ability to cast 2nd-level spells, poison use class feature.																																																							DESC:You can infuse a spell with the power of a poison.																																								ADDSPELLLEVEL:1																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.9																								BENEFIT:You can use 1 dose of poison as an additional material component for a spell you cast. This spell gains the poison descriptor (UM p.138). Select a single creature affected by the spell. If that creature fails its saving throw against the spell, it must also attempt a saving throw against the poison used as a material component. If the target fails the save against the poison, the poison takes effect immediately, ignoring any onset time. The poison uses its save DC (rather than the save DC of the spell), but is modified by any effects that increase the spell's DC (such as Spell Focus). This feat works only with spells whose effects can be negated by a successful Fortitude save. A toxic spell uses up a spell slot 1 level higher than the spell's actual level.
Treacherous Toxin			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Sneak Attack																																																																																						PRETEXT:Base attack bonus +5, sneak attack class feature.													PRETOTALAB:5																																														DESC:You twist a blade to force more of the poison on it into an enemy's bloodstream.																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.6																								BENEFIT:When you make a sneak attack with a poisoned weapon, you can forgo some of your sneak attack damage to increase the save DC of your poison, increasing the poison's save DC by 1 for every 1d6 points of sneak attack damage you forgo. This can't cause the save DC to exceed %1.|floor(TL/2)+15
Trick Spell				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Metamagic																														PREALIGN:CN	PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=1,Divine=1,Psychic=1	PREDEITY:1,Calistria																																																					PRETEXT:Ability to cast 1st-level spells, chaotic neutral alignment, worshiper of Calistria.																																																	DESCISPI:Yes				DESC:The vengeful nature of your goddess flows through your magic, turning your enemies against themselves.																																ADDSPELLLEVEL:1																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.17																								BENEFIT:Only enchantment spells that affect a single target and can be negated with a successful Will save can be trick spells. If the target fails its Will save against a trick spell, in addition to the spell's normal effects, the target also clumsily hinders itself. Immediately attempt a special combat maneuver check (1d20 + your caster level + your Charisma bonus) to perform a dirty trick combat maneuver against the target. Any feats you have that apply to dirty trick maneuvers also apply to this check. A trick spell takes up a spell slot 1 level higher than the spell's actual level.
Unseen Poison			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																																																							PRESKILL:2,Craft (Poison)=5,Bluff=5	PRESPELL:1,Nondetection	PRETEXT:Bluff 5 ranks, Craft (poison) 5 ranks, ability to cast nondetection.																																																										DESC:You can conceal the magic auras of poisons that you carry.																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.9																								BENEFIT:Whenever a creature attempts to magically detect poison you are carrying, the creature must succeed at a caster level check with a DC %1. On a failed check, that spell or magic ability fails to detect any poison you possess for the duration of the spell.|10+TL
Verify				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																														PREALIGN:LE	PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=1,Divine=1,Psychic=1	PREDEITY:1,Asmodeus																																																					PRETEXT:Ability to cast 1st-level spells, lawful evil alignment, worshiper of Asmodeus.																																																		DESCISPI:Yes				DESC:Those whom you catch breaking a deal are more subject to your powers.																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.16																								BENEFIT:You gain a +5 bonus on Sense Motive checks to determine whether a creature is lying when you ask if it has followed the terms of a contract or deal to which it formally agreed. This includes all written and signed contracts, but also such things as witnessed oaths of loyalty and guild charters. If you succeed at such a Sense Motive check and learn that a creature has violated any part of such a formal bargain, that creature takes a -2 penalty on saving throws against your spells, spell-like abilities, and supernatural abilities.
#Wasp Familiar			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																														PREALIGN:CN										PREDEITY:1,Calistria																																																					PRETEXT:Chaotic neutral alignment, worshiper of Calistria.																																													DEFINE:FamiliarMasterLVL|0	DEFINE:CalistrianFamiliar|0	DESCISPI:Yes	DESCISPI:Yes	DESC:The goddess of lust, revenge, and trickery has granted you a living sting to show her favor in you.										STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																			BONUS:VAR|FamiliarMasterLVL|TL	BONUS:VAR|CalistrianFamiliar|1	BONUS:VAR|CalistrianFamiliar|1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Arcane Bond ~ Familiar,Witch ~ Familiar	FOLLOWERS:Familiar|1	COMPANIONLIST:Familiar|Familiar (Wasp (Giant))	COMPANIONLIST:Familiar|Familiar (Wasp (Calistrian))|PREVARGTEQ:CalistrianFamiliar,2	SOURCEPAGE:p.17																								BENEFIT:You gain familiar as per the arcane bond class feature, using your character level as your wizard level. The familiar is a cat-sized, chaotic neutral wasp loyal to you. If you have the ability to gain a familiar through other means (such as the arcane bond class feature), and you are at least 5th level, instead gain a Calistrian wasp. You can have only one familiar. If you ever grossly violate the code of conduct required by Calistria (a violation of the scale that would cause a cleric of Calistria to lose all spells and class features), your familiar turns on you and attacks you until it is killed. To regain a familiar, you must atone for your deeds with the atonement spell, and pay to have the slain familiar raised from the dead. If your familiar is slain or lost through other means, you can replace it using the normal rules for replacing familiars. Special: This feat can be taken a second time by characters of 7th or higher level if they do not otherwise have access to familiars. Such characters have access to a Calistrian wasp.

